Steven Nelms writes that he 'can't afford' his wife to be stay-at-home mom . 
 He calculates the monetary value of what she contributes to the home, including child care, cooking, cleaning and running the finances . 
 Nelms concludes that his wife's annual salary should be $73,960 . 
 He writes that he was 'ashamed' that his wife ever 'felt like she doesn't have just as much right to our income as I do'Nelms said his wife has worked since she was 14 and he wanted to make sure she felt appreciated . 
 